{"title_page": "Bolivia", "text_new": "{{About|the South American country}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n<!--{{pp-move|small=yes}}-->\n{{short description|Landlocked country in South America}}\n{{Use American English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{coord|-16.712|-64.666|format=dms|region:BO|display=title}}\n{{Infobox country\n| conventional_long_name                = Plurinational State of Bolivia\n| common_name                = Bolivia\n| native_name                = {{small|{{nobold|{{native name|es|Estado Plurinacional de Bolivia}}<br />{{native name|gn|Tet\u00e3 Het\u00e3voregua Mborivia}}<br />{{native name|ay|Wuliwya Suyu}}<br />{{native name|qu|Puliwya Mamallaqta}}<!--end nobold:-->}}}}\n| image_flag                = Flag of Bolivia.svg\n| image_coat                = Escudo de Bolivia.svg\n| national_motto                = {{native phrase|es|\"La Uni\u00f3n es la Fuerza\"|italics=off|nolink=yes}}<br/>{{small|\"Unity is Strength\"}}{{lower|0.2em|<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bcb.gov.bo/sitio/monedas/ligera/monedas/m10c.html | title=Moneda de 10 Centavos |trans-title=10 Cent Coins | language=Spanish | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070428004356/http://www.bcb.gov.bo/sitio/monedas/ligera/monedas/m10c.html | archivedate=28 April 2007 | publisher=[[Central Bank of Bolivia]] | accessdate=28 January 2014}}</ref>}}\n| national_anthem                = {{native name|es|\"[[National Anthem of Bolivia|Himno Nacional de Bolivia]]\"|nolink=yes|italic=no}}<br/><center>[[File:Himno Nacional de Bolivia instrumental.ogg]]</center>\n| image_map                = BOL orthographic.svg\n| map_width                = 220px\n| alt_map                = \n| image_map2                = Bolivia - Location Map (2011) - BOL - UNOCHA.svg\n| alt_map2                = \n| map_caption                = {{map caption |location_color=dark green |region=[[South America]] |region_color= grey }}\n| capital                = [[Sucre]] <small>(constitutional and judicial)</small><br/>[[La Paz]] <small>(executive and legislative)</small>\n| largest_city                = {{nowrap|[[Santa Cruz de la Sierra]]}}<br/>{{small|{{coord|17|48|S|63|10|W}}}}\n| languages_type                = Official languages<ref name=\"languages\">{{cite web|url=http://bolivia.justia.com/nacionales/nueva-constitucion-politica-del-estado/primera-parte/titulo-i/capitulo-primero/|title=Justia Bolivia :: Nueva Constituci\u00f3n Pol\u00edtica Del Estado > PRIMERA PARTE > T\u00cdTULO I > CAP\u00cdTULO PRIMERO :: Ley de Bolivia|website=bolivia.justia.com|access-date=24 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170225051614/http://bolivia.justia.com/nacionales/nueva-constitucion-politica-del-estado/primera-parte/titulo-i/capitulo-primero/|archive-date=25 February 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| languages                = {{collapsible list\n  |titlestyle = background:transparent;text-align:left;font-weight:normal;\n  |title = [[Bolivian Spanish|Spanish]] |[[Aymara language|Aymara]] | [[Araona language|Araona]] | [[Baure language|Baure]] | [[B\u00e9siro language|B\u00e9siro]] | [[Canichana language|Canichana]] | [[Cavine\u00f1o language|Cavine\u00f1o]] | [[Cayubaba language|Cayubaba]] | [[Ch\u00e1cobo language|Ch\u00e1cobo]] | [[Chim\u00e1n language|Chim\u00e1n]] | [[Ese Ejja language|Ese Ejja]] | [[Guaran\u00ed language|Guaran\u00ed]] | [[Guarasu'we language|Guarasu'we]] | [[Guarayu language|Guarayu]] | [[Itonama language|Itonama]] | [[Leco language|Leco]] | [[Machajuyai-kallawaya language|Machajuyai-kallawaya]] | [[Machineri language|Machineri]] | [[Maropa language|Maropa]] | [[Moje\u00f1otrinitario language|Moje\u00f1otrinitario]] | [[Moje\u00f1o-ignaciano language|Moje\u00f1o-ignaciano]] | [[Mor\u00e9 language|Mor\u00e9]] | [[Moset\u00e9n language|Moset\u00e9n]] | [[Movima language|Movima]] | [[Pacawara language|Pacawara]] | [[Puquina language|Puquina]] | [[Quechua language|Quechua]] | [[Sirion\u00f3 language|Sirion\u00f3]] | [[Tacana language|Tacana]] | [[Tapiete language|Tapiete]] | [[Toromona language|Toromona]] | [[Uruchipaya language|Uruchipaya]] | [[Weenhayek language|Weenhayek]] | [[Yaminawa language|Yaminawa]] | [[Yuki language|Yuki]] | [[Yuracar\u00e9 language|Yuracar\u00e9]] | [[Zamuco language|Zamuco]]\n }}\n| ethnic_groups                = {{unbulleted list\n |68% [[Mestizo]]\n |20% [[Indigenous Bolivians|Indigenous]]\n |5% [[White Bolivians|White]]\n |1% [[Afro-Bolivians|Black]] \n |4% Other\n |2% Unspecified \n}}\n| ethnic_groups_year                = 2018<ref name=\"cia\">{{cite web | url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bl.html | title=South America :: Bolivia | work=[[The World Factbook]] | publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency]] | accessdate=25 March 2017 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110213095613/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bl.html | archive-date=13 February 2011 | url-status=live | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n| demonym                = Bolivian\n| government_type                = [[Unitary state|Unitary]] [[Presidential system|presidential]] [[Republic|constitutional republic]] under a foreign-backed [[coup de tat]]\n| leader_title1                = [[President of Bolivia]], unseated by \u00c1\u00f1ez coup\n| leader_name1                 = [[Evo Morales]]\n| leader_title2                = ''Illegitimate president of coup government''\n| leader_name2                 = [[Jeanine \u00c1\u00f1ez]]\n| legislature                = [[Plurinational Legislative Assembly]]\n| upper_house                = [[Chamber of Senators (Bolivia)|Chamber of Senators]]\n| lower_house                = [[Chamber of Deputies (Bolivia)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| sovereignty_type                = [[Bolivian Declaration of Independence|Independence]]\n| sovereignty_note                = from [[Spain]]\n| established_event1                = Declared\n| established_date1                = 6 August 1825\n| established_event2        